section.section:
Of the twelve Board members:
Ten shall be licensed pharmacists, including:
Two who at the time of appointment practice primarily in chain store pharmacies;
Two who at the time of appointment practice primarily in independent pharmacies;
Two who at the time of appointment practice primarily in an acute-care hospital;
One who at the time of appointment practices primarily in a pharmacy that provides services to a long-term care facility;
One who at the time of appointment practices primarily in a pharmacy that specializes in the provision of home infusion/home care services; and
Two pharmacists at-large; and
Two shall be consumer members.

text.section:
Each consumer member of the Board:
Shall be a member of the general public;
May not be or ever have been a pharmacist or in training to become a pharmacist;
May not have a household member who is a pharmacist or in training to become a pharmacist;
May not participate or ever have participated in a commercial or professional field related to practicing pharmacy;
May not have a household member who participates in a commercial or professional field related to practicing pharmacy; and
May not have had within 2 years before appointment a substantial financial interest in a person regulated by the Board.
